00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:39.570
and everything.

00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:44.820
And there's a particular topic
that I was really caught by

00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:49.500
and really dragged my attention
into, which is,

00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:51.790
today, we see a lot of new
applications coming up.

00:02:51.790 --> 00:02:54.860
We have tons of applications
coming up every day.

00:02:54.860 --> 00:02:57.520
We have very popular
applications that are coming

00:02:57.520 --> 00:02:58.690
to Android.

00:02:58.690 --> 00:03:01.890
And people discuss about whether
they are using the

00:03:01.890 --> 00:03:04.800
right patterns, whether they
should use the right pattern,

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:06.260
if they are not using
the right pattern,

00:03:06.260 --> 00:03:08.180
and things like that.

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:11.520
There's a particular question
that comes up once in a while.

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:15.290
And it really made me think
about it, which is, if every

00:03:15.290 --> 00:03:18.440
application is using the style
guide, it doesn't mean we're

00:03:18.440 --> 00:03:21.680
going to have all applications
look the same.

00:03:21.680 --> 00:03:23.970
Well, the answer is,
obviously, not.

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:25.710
Quite the opposite, actually.

00:03:25.710 --> 00:03:29.640
I really believe that Android
is the ecosystem out there

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:33.820
that offers the maximum
flexibility to really make

00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:37.400
your brand to shine and be
different from all the other

00:03:37.400 --> 00:03:39.780
applications in the market.

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.770
So there's something very
important that we need to

00:03:41.770 --> 00:03:43.180
understand.

00:03:43.180 --> 00:03:46.500
Being consistent and adapting
the right pattern to your

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:49.680
application, it doesn't mean
that your application has to

00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:52.120
be looking the same
like others.

00:03:52.120 --> 00:03:53.820
You have many, many
ways to make your

00:03:53.820 --> 00:03:55.360
application to look special.

00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:59.210
I mean, who would like to have
an ecosystem just to be very

00:03:59.210 --> 00:04:01.330
boring and looking the same?

00:04:01.330 --> 00:04:02.750
Think about human beings.

00:04:02.750 --> 00:04:04.770
We're all different.

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:07.700
If you look around, there's no
one that looks like you.

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:10.070
We also dress up differently to

00:04:10.070 --> 00:04:12.382
distinguish from one another.

00:04:12.382 --> 00:04:15.330
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:15.330 --> 00:04:20.860
When we're outside Google I/O.
And I think this is the way

00:04:20.860 --> 00:04:25.220
that I'd like our ecosystems to
be, to have very different

00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:25.700
application.

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:29.290
At the same time, human beings
have very consistent patterns,

00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:31.120
even if you don't speak the
language of someone else.

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:34.040
I'm sure people here come
from all over the world.

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:35.440
I come from Italy.

00:04:35.440 --> 00:04:37.760
And we may not know
the same language.

00:04:37.760 --> 00:04:41.240
But if I smile, or if I get
angry, or if I raise up my

00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:44.220
voice, people do understand
what I mean.

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:47.410
And so we want our application
to have that standard,

00:04:47.410 --> 00:04:53.350
consistent way of behaving to be
consistent across Android.

00:04:53.350 --> 00:04:55.110
So how do we do it?

00:04:55.110 --> 00:04:59.030
Well, the style guide is a great
example of how you need

00:04:59.030 --> 00:05:01.100
to make certain things
very consistent.

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:04.400
Because when they're not
consistent, we just break the

00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:06.190
user maintained model.

00:05:06.190 --> 00:05:08.360
Learning an ecosystem, learning
an operating system

00:05:08.360 --> 00:05:09.040
is difficult.

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:11.320
You start playing with it, you
start swiping around, you

00:05:11.320 --> 00:05:12.190
start learning some gestures.

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:15.080
And when not all the
applications use them

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:17.230
consistently, then you
just don't know how

00:05:17.230 --> 00:05:19.440
to operate any more.

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:21.500
So you want to know where
my settings are.

00:05:21.500 --> 00:05:24.070
You want to know that, if I see
different views next to

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:26.860
each other, I can swipe
through it.

00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:28.800
You want to know where the
action bar is with all the

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:30.250
main actions.

00:05:30.250 --> 00:05:32.810
But at the same time, you
want to make it special.

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:34.630
And there are ways to do it.

00:05:34.630 --> 00:05:36.610
You can play with graphics.

00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:38.400
You can play with gradients.

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:39.870
It's not true that all
applications on

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:41.750
Android has to be flat.

00:05:41.750 --> 00:05:44.250
Like we like the style, so we
adopt it that way in the core

00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:44.890
applications.

00:05:44.890 --> 00:05:49.590
But, by any means, if your brand
is soft and wants to

00:05:49.590 --> 00:05:52.000
have gradients and little
treatment in the action bars

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:53.960
and across the UI,
that's welcome.

00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:57.140
We want an ecosystem to
be very different.

00:05:57.140 --> 00:06:01.110
The way your little elements
animate from one another, if I

00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:04.020
tap on a list view, how does it
zoom into a full view, this

00:06:04.020 --> 00:06:05.740
is all up to you.

00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:09.260
And I think the more,
the merrier.

00:06:09.260 --> 00:06:12.140
The more diversity we can find
in our ecosystem, the more

00:06:12.140 --> 00:06:14.590
people are going to find little
special things to make

00:06:14.590 --> 00:06:17.070
their application even
more interesting.

00:06:17.070 --> 00:06:20.400
And I love to see it
when it happens.

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:21.600
So this is why we're here.

00:06:21.600 --> 00:06:24.570
We want to deliver this
simple message.

00:06:24.570 --> 00:06:28.660
Designing for Android allows you
to have applications that

00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:32.610
feels unique, that
feels beautiful.

00:06:32.610 --> 00:06:33.660
And at the same time,
they're very

00:06:33.660 --> 00:06:36.230
consistent and easy to use.

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:39.360
So to do that, this time we
organize the workshop.

00:06:39.360 --> 00:06:41.400
In fact, this is not
really a talk.

00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:42.650
I don't even have slides.

