00:50:29.410 --> 00:50:33.905
AUDIENCE: In terms of user
experience and design, how do

00:50:33.905 --> 00:50:35.520
you deal with all
their platforms?

00:50:35.520 --> 00:50:38.190
Do you think it's better to
style everything to have the

00:50:38.190 --> 00:50:42.930
same user experience across
other devices as well?

00:50:42.930 --> 00:50:46.180
Or do you leverage whatever the
platform is offering you?

00:50:46.180 --> 00:50:50.640
For instance, take the example
of dialogs or edit text or

00:50:50.640 --> 00:50:53.215
check boxes, do you have
the same style for all?

00:50:53.215 --> 00:50:56.280
Or how do you deal with that?

00:50:56.280 --> 00:51:00.730
MICHAEL NOVAK: For GigBeat, we
style the dialogues, but we

00:51:00.730 --> 00:51:03.070
use wherever the platform
base is.

00:51:03.070 --> 00:51:05.490
So for Holo, we use the Holo
dialogue as a base.

00:51:05.490 --> 00:51:08.980
And for Gingerbread and lower,
we use the regular theme as a

00:51:08.980 --> 00:51:09.920
dialogue base.

00:51:09.920 --> 00:51:11.190
And we do change the color.

00:51:11.190 --> 00:51:15.330
But we didn't port back a lot
of the drawable assets like

00:51:15.330 --> 00:51:18.480
the progress bar or the progress
indicator, we just

00:51:18.480 --> 00:51:20.060
used whatever is on
the platform for

00:51:20.060 --> 00:51:21.450
that particular device.

00:51:21.450 --> 00:51:23.162
AUDIENCE: OK, thank you.

00:51:23.162 --> 00:51:24.550
