01:08:58.020 --> 01:09:00.430
Part of this app, what I really
like, is that you have

01:09:00.430 --> 01:09:01.319
multiple themes.

01:09:01.319 --> 01:09:03.710
And it's always hard to
be a visual designer.

01:09:03.710 --> 01:09:06.180
And the way you have to do it
is it's easy to include

01:09:06.180 --> 01:09:07.450
everything and have
multiple themes.

01:09:07.450 --> 01:09:09.660
But what you really need to do
it on is figure out your

01:09:09.660 --> 01:09:12.220
brand, and then just go
with that one theme.

01:09:12.220 --> 01:09:15.040
So you have colorful
gradients.

01:09:15.040 --> 01:09:18.300
You have brushed metal and these
luster, shiny icons.

01:09:18.300 --> 01:09:21.680
And I'm wondering if you could
actually take what you did in

01:09:21.680 --> 01:09:23.760
the dashboard with those icons,
those metal icons, and

01:09:23.760 --> 01:09:26.270
explore that theme and made that
the focus of everything.

01:09:26.270 --> 01:09:29.270
And that Today's app would
become a chrome icon, too.

01:09:29.270 --> 01:09:33.300
And then, maybe, your action bar
could be chromed out, too.

01:09:33.300 --> 01:09:36.200
You create this illusion
of life that it doesn't

01:09:36.200 --> 01:09:38.300
necessarily mean that everything
becomes a bookshelf

01:09:38.300 --> 01:09:41.160
or anything like you mimic
the real world.

01:09:41.160 --> 01:09:44.569
But it actually means that you
create these elements and you

01:09:44.569 --> 01:09:46.560
establish these relationships
where they could actually live

01:09:46.560 --> 01:09:47.819
in the same world together.

01:09:47.819 --> 01:09:49.620
And then people aren't--

01:09:49.620 --> 01:09:53.109
a constant analogy I always have
is that like I just saw

01:09:53.109 --> 01:09:55.270
Prometheus, the sci-fi movie.

01:09:55.270 --> 01:09:57.770
And when I see aliens, I'm
totally freaked out.

01:09:57.770 --> 01:10:00.710
But then, an hour later, I'm
like, oh, this is just a

01:10:00.710 --> 01:10:04.780
really cruel, weird world that
these monsters live in.

01:10:04.780 --> 01:10:05.970
And I'm not freaked
out any more.

01:10:05.970 --> 01:10:10.510
So once you start establishing
these relationships with icons

01:10:10.510 --> 01:10:13.540
and the elements and, as a user,
when you enter it and

01:10:13.540 --> 01:10:16.790
you realize that these things
can actually have a

01:10:16.790 --> 01:10:19.470
relationship, it's
a nice feeling.

01:10:19.470 --> 01:10:21.320
You don't feel like you're
shocked every single time you

01:10:21.320 --> 01:10:24.560
turn a page or enter a new
state of the page.

01:10:24.560 --> 01:10:26.030
MIKE WOLFSON: So to just
