01:10:57.170 --> 01:10:59.610
This is one of my personal,
pet crusades.

01:10:59.610 --> 01:11:02.910
I always talk about this, which
is the sometimes less is

01:11:02.910 --> 01:11:04.380
actually more.

01:11:04.380 --> 01:11:09.150
And I have two different types
of wars that I like to wage.

01:11:09.150 --> 01:11:13.000
And one is a war against text
junk, the unnecessary

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:17.530
typographic elements that are
intended to clarify things,

01:11:17.530 --> 01:11:20.760
but where, actually, space and
contrast and color actually

01:11:20.760 --> 01:11:23.210
make a better impact.

01:11:23.210 --> 01:11:26.950
And also label junk, where,
again, context can provide

01:11:26.950 --> 01:11:28.910
much of the same function.

01:11:28.910 --> 01:11:31.460
So one of the things I'd suggest
you might think about

01:11:31.460 --> 01:11:35.080
is, when you look at all those
section headings, they're very

01:11:35.080 --> 01:11:37.150
effective as section headings,
because you've used the color

01:11:37.150 --> 01:11:40.070
contrast, so they don't all
need to have that colon

01:11:40.070 --> 01:11:41.370
following them.

01:11:41.370 --> 01:11:44.140
Again, when you have things like
the cost of the app or

01:11:44.140 --> 01:11:47.620
the size or the rating, you
might not even need to have

01:11:47.620 --> 01:11:50.010
labels on many of those things,
because the data

01:11:50.010 --> 01:11:52.600
itself can carry that context.

01:11:52.600 --> 01:11:54.500
You represent the rating
as stars, maybe.

01:11:54.500 --> 01:11:57.010
And then, again, it becomes
very obvious what it is.

01:11:57.010 --> 01:11:59.710
So take a look throughout all
your apps and think about

01:11:59.710 --> 01:12:03.220
which elements are really
just gilding the lily.

01:12:03.220 --> 01:12:05.850
You'll find that taking them out
allows you to really focus

01:12:05.850 --> 01:12:06.495
more on the content.

01:12:06.495 --> 01:12:07.740
MIKE WOLFSON: That's
