01:13:08.550 --> 01:13:11.620
So this is Papyrus.

01:13:11.620 --> 01:13:15.690
It is a natural handwriting
note-taking application.

01:13:15.690 --> 01:13:19.160
I designed it initially
for 10-inch tablets.

01:13:19.160 --> 01:13:22.860
And we're slowly trying to work
the interface down to

01:13:22.860 --> 01:13:24.550
smaller devices.

01:13:24.550 --> 01:13:29.230
So this is running on
a ThinkPad tablet.

01:13:29.230 --> 01:13:34.230
How many people know what active
pen technology is?

01:13:34.230 --> 01:13:34.970
A few people.

01:13:34.970 --> 01:13:35.640
OK.

01:13:35.640 --> 01:13:40.410
So natural handwriting is--

01:13:40.410 --> 01:13:42.690
basically, this app allows you
to write just like you would

01:13:42.690 --> 01:13:46.330
write on paper, but with all
of the advantages of modern

01:13:46.330 --> 01:13:47.890
technology, like in tablets.

01:13:47.890 --> 01:13:49.780
So with an active pen--

01:13:54.020 --> 01:13:57.250
thank you-- that comes with this
device, it's different

01:13:57.250 --> 01:14:00.370
than a capacitive stylus that
works on just any tablet.

01:14:00.370 --> 01:14:02.170
It's a lot more accurate.

01:14:02.170 --> 01:14:04.420
And it has a lot more
data throughput.

01:14:04.420 --> 01:14:07.260
It can detect when it's near
the device, pressure

01:14:07.260 --> 01:14:09.150
sensitive, it has
side buttons.

01:14:09.150 --> 01:14:10.840
Others have more side buttons.

01:14:10.840 --> 01:14:16.870
So for example, if I open a
note here, I can write.

01:14:16.870 --> 01:14:18.250
And it works really
well with me.

01:14:21.790 --> 01:14:23.900
So if I have it bigger, you
can see the pressure

01:14:23.900 --> 01:14:24.600
sensitivity there.

01:14:24.600 --> 01:14:28.520
So it allows for a much more
natural handwriting.

01:14:28.520 --> 01:14:32.550
So basically, the application
has notebooks on the left and

01:14:32.550 --> 01:14:33.440
notes on the right.

