01:14:51.870 --> 01:14:55.840
So when you wrote to us, you
were asking us about the

01:14:55.840 --> 01:14:57.550
general navigation.

01:14:57.550 --> 01:15:00.530
It feels like having to have
this navigation with a

01:15:00.530 --> 01:15:02.120
split-screen, it's kind of

01:15:02.120 --> 01:15:05.210
challenging on smaller devices.

01:15:05.210 --> 01:15:07.000
And I thought it was a very
interesting point.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:11.690
In fact, actually, also I was
excited when you applied for

01:15:11.690 --> 01:15:14.290
this workshop, because I do
use this application.

01:15:14.290 --> 01:15:16.700
And the beauty of this
application is that it's all

01:15:16.700 --> 01:15:18.600
about gestures.

01:15:18.600 --> 01:15:20.510
You have two fingers.

01:15:20.510 --> 01:15:22.230
You move your canvas
with two fingers.

01:15:22.230 --> 01:15:23.530
You pinch the zoom.

01:15:23.530 --> 01:15:25.810
You control with your pen.

01:15:25.810 --> 01:15:28.280
You can erase with
your finger.

01:15:28.280 --> 01:15:29.860
It's just beautiful.

01:15:29.860 --> 01:15:36.340
And then I felt, maybe, a way
to get this kind of screen,

01:15:36.340 --> 01:15:39.420
the split-screen, to work on
different devices, on smaller

01:15:39.420 --> 01:15:42.640
screens could be to maybe having
it slide like a lot of

01:15:42.640 --> 01:15:44.330
applications do today.

01:15:44.330 --> 01:15:46.620
But then, at the same time,
I wonder whether

01:15:46.620 --> 01:15:48.260
there are other options.

01:15:48.260 --> 01:15:50.880
Like maybe you don't need
the split-screen at all.

01:15:50.880 --> 01:15:52.400
Why don't we make
the navigation

01:15:52.400 --> 01:15:55.050
to be purely gestural.

01:15:55.050 --> 01:15:58.160
So that, when I get
my application,

01:15:58.160 --> 01:15:59.500
I see all my notebooks.

01:15:59.500 --> 01:16:00.600
And then I tap on them.

01:16:00.600 --> 01:16:03.260
And they open up in all
the pages that I have.

01:16:03.260 --> 01:16:06.180
And perhaps I can pinch to
get back to my notebooks.

01:16:06.180 --> 01:16:09.210
And everything just becomes
super gestural.

01:16:09.210 --> 01:16:13.740
So that's something that I think
we need to consider.

01:16:13.740 --> 01:16:16.740
Not every application must have
a split-screen or this

01:16:16.740 --> 01:16:17.720
standard navigation.

01:16:17.720 --> 01:16:20.580
I think we can really innovate
in the way we get into

01:16:20.580 --> 01:16:22.730
different views.

01:16:22.730 --> 01:16:26.460
I guess the pattern that we
already have, which is similar

01:16:26.460 --> 01:16:28.570
to what I'm talking about,
this gallery, where the

01:16:28.570 --> 01:16:30.610
navigation is purely
hierarchical, you don't have

01:16:30.610 --> 01:16:32.460
any split-screen.

01:16:32.460 --> 01:16:34.951
Tell me what you think
about that.

01:16:34.951 --> 01:16:38.090
ANDREW HUGHES: Yeah,
I want to utilize

01:16:38.090 --> 01:16:40.180
gestures as much as possible.

01:16:40.180 --> 01:16:43.390
So with a pen right now--

01:16:43.390 --> 01:16:46.000
I know you were talking about
the general layout of the

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:54.050
app-- but in the note taking,
you can use gestures to undo.

01:16:54.050 --> 01:16:56.510
