But there's a lot of
things that you

01:58:35.820 --> 01:58:37.310
can do on this screen.

01:58:37.310 --> 01:58:39.480
If I look at it, there's--

01:58:39.480 --> 01:58:42.520
just for the one key action that
I'm most interested in,

01:58:42.520 --> 01:58:45.220
which is getting a picture
loaded up to start the

01:58:45.220 --> 01:58:47.810
blending process, I've
got six buttons.

01:58:47.810 --> 01:58:50.750
I've got the big, nice
affordance of the picture

01:58:50.750 --> 01:58:53.390
frame, which is where my finger
just is magnetically

01:58:53.390 --> 01:58:54.810
attracted to touch.

01:58:54.810 --> 01:58:56.670
And then I have the Camera
button, and I

01:58:56.670 --> 01:58:57.530
have a Facebook button.

01:58:57.530 --> 01:58:59.910
These are all different ways
of loading up a picture.

01:58:59.910 --> 01:59:02.140
And I have each one of those
for both pictures.

01:59:02.140 --> 01:59:04.840
I've got six different buttons
that I have to look at when

01:59:04.840 --> 01:59:06.200
I'm looking at this screen.

01:59:06.200 --> 01:59:09.570
Which can be a little
intimidating, perhaps.

01:59:09.570 --> 01:59:13.290
And also, I just have to think a
lot harder than I want to to

01:59:13.290 --> 01:59:15.690
work with a fun application.

01:59:15.690 --> 01:59:18.990
So I think I think one of the
things that you should think

01:59:18.990 --> 01:59:21.350
about doing with this
application is really trying

01:59:21.350 --> 01:59:26.090
to get right into taking
that first picture.

01:59:26.090 --> 01:59:29.710
Jumping right into the big
picture frame, before you show

01:59:29.710 --> 01:59:32.910
any of your file manipulation
stuff.

01:59:32.910 --> 01:59:34.700
Jump right into here.

01:59:34.700 --> 01:59:37.780
Show a big picture, maybe show
a button that helps you to

01:59:37.780 --> 01:59:39.950
understand a secondary action.

01:59:39.950 --> 01:59:42.660
I mean, one of the themes, I
think, that at least we've

01:59:42.660 --> 01:59:45.170
been saying for most of the apps
that we've looked at so

01:59:45.170 --> 01:59:47.370
far today is that
less is more--

01:59:47.370 --> 01:59:50.340
that the more you can pull out
of your UI, the more you can

01:59:50.340 --> 01:59:53.410
make decisions about what's the
most important aspect, the

01:59:53.410 --> 01:59:55.570
better off I think you're
going to be.

01:59:55.570 --> 02:00:01.250
So I would look at those six
actions that you've got there.

