OREN BENGIGI: Oh,
like a result?

02:00:08.070 --> 02:00:11.110
You go from screen to screen?

02:00:11.110 --> 02:00:11.720
JEREMY LYON: Yeah.

02:00:11.720 --> 02:00:13.540
Yeah, that's one option.

02:00:13.540 --> 02:00:15.540
You want to draw a
little bit, Rich?

02:00:15.540 --> 02:00:18.620
Rich is going to save you all
from seeing my completely

02:00:18.620 --> 02:00:19.870
illegible scribbling.

02:00:22.460 --> 02:00:25.600
And another option can think
about here is, are all three

02:00:25.600 --> 02:00:28.975
of those ways of getting an
image equally important?

02:00:31.960 --> 02:00:34.270
You probably have a better
idea how users use this

02:00:34.270 --> 02:00:34.790
application.

02:00:34.790 --> 02:00:38.060
But I would argue that using the
camera to take a picture,

02:00:38.060 --> 02:00:39.500
that's what I want
