And sometimes face detection
goes wrong, so you can go and

02:04:31.360 --> 02:04:32.990
edit blend.

02:04:32.990 --> 02:04:39.740
And you can just manually adjust
the detected face, and

02:04:39.740 --> 02:04:45.690
do it to the other
face, like this.

02:04:45.690 --> 02:04:49.340
And once you hit Apply, it
reblends the faces, and you

02:04:49.340 --> 02:04:50.075
get a better result.

02:04:50.075 --> 02:04:53.050
Or worse, I don't know.

02:04:53.050 --> 02:04:54.790
RICHARD FULCHER: I think I've
become a V For Vendetta mask.

02:04:57.780 --> 02:04:59.210
A Ugnaught.

02:04:59.210 --> 02:05:01.840
JEREMY LYON: Well, there might
be some ways to get those same

02:05:01.840 --> 02:05:05.660
kinds of actions available to
you, even using your own

02:05:05.660 --> 02:05:06.890
custom background.

