But one of the things you can
do with action bar-- action

02:05:09.770 --> 02:05:13.710
bar doesn't need to use the
framework gray background.

02:05:13.710 --> 02:05:15.490
You can actually use a
transparent background.

02:05:15.490 --> 02:05:17.330
So you can keep your own
background image there, the

02:05:17.330 --> 02:05:20.260
one that you've had earlier,
and draw that there.

02:05:20.260 --> 02:05:24.850
Likewise, you can change the
font for your app title there.

02:05:24.850 --> 02:05:26.925
You could use the same font that
you were using earlier so

02:05:26.925 --> 02:05:29.010
you keep that consistency.

02:05:29.010 --> 02:05:33.040
And I might look at something
instead of tabs, which are

02:05:33.040 --> 02:05:36.570
effective ways of jumping
between these three screens.

02:05:36.570 --> 02:05:39.050
But going back to what Rich was
drawing, you might think

02:05:39.050 --> 02:05:41.720
about doing this sort of more
direct manipulation.

02:05:41.720 --> 02:05:44.040
I don't know if part of what you
were trying to do here was

02:05:44.040 --> 02:05:49.270
make this image as big as
possible in this view, but you

02:05:49.270 --> 02:05:53.410
might be able to sacrifice a
little bit of space around the

02:05:53.410 --> 02:05:56.840
edges to kind of hint at the A
and the B on either side, or

02:05:56.840 --> 02:05:58.440
perhaps it's a linear
progression--

02:05:58.440 --> 02:06:00.090
I don't know what the right
approach is here--

02:06:00.090 --> 02:06:02.330
where you can directly
manipulate, just swapping

02:06:02.330 --> 02:06:05.790
between the two starting
pictures

02:06:05.790 --> 02:06:07.320
and the blended picture.

02:06:07.320 --> 02:06:10.120
And if you chose to use the
action bar throughout your

02:06:10.120 --> 02:06:13.090
application, even in the earlier
screens that we saw,

02:06:13.090 --> 02:06:17.670
and maintain that playfulness
with the transparency and the

02:06:17.670 --> 02:06:21.720
font changes on the title, you
could put in there your

02:06:21.720 --> 02:06:22.700
overflow menu.

02:06:22.700 --> 02:06:25.570
And that gives you a place to
put things like Load and

02:06:25.570 --> 02:06:29.040
Delete and the actions that
perhaps you don't want to give

02:06:29.040 --> 02:06:30.980
the same kind of prominence to
when you're really trying to

02:06:30.980 --> 02:06:33.570
get someone just to have fun and
start taking pictures, but

02:06:33.570 --> 02:06:36.450
you need to have available
to the user there.

02:06:36.450 --> 02:06:37.310
OREN BENGIGI: Yeah, I agree.

02:06:37.310 --> 02:06:40.482
The interface here is too
serious, I think, for--

02:06:40.482 --> 02:06:42.785
JEREMY LYON: This screen, yes.

